Head of DPRK Delegation Reiterates DPRK's Stand on Denuclearization of Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government maintains its consistent position to resolve the issue of denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula peacefully. Choe Su Hon, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs who is leading the DPRK delegation, declared this at the plenary session of the 61st General Assembly of the United Nations on Sept. 26.
 Referring to the necessity and justice of the Songun policy of Kim Jong Il, he said that the Songun policy provides a sure guarantee for safeguarding the sovereignty and security of the country and ensuring peace and security on the Korean Peninsula and the rest of the region, given the evermore undisguised U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's possession of powerful deterrent solely meant for self-defense is in full line with the interests of the regional countries in peace and security and peaceful environment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As well known to the world, the important points stipulated in the Joint Statement adopted at the Six-Party Talks on September 19, 2005 are the commitment made by the DPRK to abandon its nuclear program and the U.S. commitment to co-exist with the former in peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK remains committed to implementing all the agreed provisions of the Joint Statement on an equal footing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, the U.S., soon after the announcement of the Joint Statement, lost no time to impose financial sanctions upon the DPRK, a dialogue partner, eventually scrapping the already-agreed itinerary for the following rounds of the talks and creating the present impasse. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All these facts clearly indicate that the U.S. is not in favor of both the Six-Party Talks and the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Turning to the issue of the expansion of permanent membership of the UN Security Council, he stated that the UN member countries should not allow under any circumstances such a country as Japan to sit on the council as it is a war criminal which invaded Asian countries and massacred innocent civilians and, worse still, has worked hard to distort its history of aggression, instead of settling it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government of the DPRK will continue in the future, too, to develop the relations of friendship and cooperation with all member states that respect its sovereignty in accordance with the idea of its foreign policy: independence, peace and friendship and make a positive contribution to the efforts of the international community to achieve world peace and security and sustainable development, he concluded.

Reception Given on 57th Anniversary of PRC 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and the Central Committee of the Korea-China Friendship Association hosted a reception at the Chongryu Restaurant on Thursday on the occasion of the 57th founding anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
 Present on invitation were Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Liu Xiaoming and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, in his speech said that the foundation of the PRC was a brilliant victory achieved by the Chinese people through their long and arduous struggle under the guidance of the Communist Party of China and a historic event which brought about a radical change in the destiny of the Chinese people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chinese people are now achieving great successes in their efforts to build a comprehensively well-off society under the leadership of the CPC with respected Hu Jintao as its general secretary and the international position of China is daily being enhancing, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are rejoiced over this and wish the Chinese people greater success in their efforts to strengthen the national power and achieve reunification of the whole country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent stand of the Workers' Party of Korea and the DPRK government to develop Korea-China friendly and cooperative relations. We, together with the Chinese comrades, will make positive efforts to develop the friendly relations between the two countries in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Liu Xiaoming in his speech said that they, together with the Korean people, significantly celebrated the 58th birthday of the DPRK a few days ago. The Chinese people, he pointed out, are rejoiced over the great successes achieved by the Korean people in socialist construction under the wise guidance of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il after the foundation of the DPRK and wish the fraternal Korean people greater success in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The traditional China-Korea friendship was forged by the elder revolutionaries of the two countries and it is the steadfast policy of the Chinese party and government to continuously boost the Sino-Korean relations of friendship and cooperation, he added.

U.S. Sinister Aim of "Transfer of Right to Command Wartime Operations" Disclosed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The U.S. and south Korea are now discussing the issue of "transfer of the right to command the wartime operations". What the U.S. seeks through this is to accelerate the preparations for a war of aggression against the north. 
 Minju Joson Friday observes this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a matter of fact, the U.S. is amassing hardware for preemptive attacks such as Aegis craft in waters off south Korea and its vicinity under the signboard of "transfer of the right to command wartime operations." It is against this backdrop that north-targeted war maneuvers never cease there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is pressurizing the south Koran authorities to stage more war exercises while accelerating its preparations for a war against the north under the above-mentioned signboard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is using the "transfer of the right to command the wartime operations" as a pretext for strengthening its politico-military domination over south Korea and hurling its troops as a shock brigade and bullet-shields of the U.S. forces in the war against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Anyone in whose vein runs the blood of the Korean nation is duty-bound to see through the U.S. sinister aim to pit Koreans against themselves and demand the withdrawal of its forces from south Korea. This being a hard reality, the south Korean military authorities are busy introducing ultra-modern weapons such as Aegis craft, early-warning control plane, military spy satellite and new-type fighters, describing "the process of taking back the right to command the wartime operations" as something for "self-reliant national defence".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
ï¿½@The arms build-up stepped up by the south Koran authorities under the above-said pretext is an outrageous military provocation against the army and people of the DPRK and, at the same time, a blatant mockery and insult to the south Korean people aspiring after independence and peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the south Korean authorities truly stand for "self-reliant national defence", they should stop supporting the outside forces but opt for national cooperation aimed at driving the aggressors out of south Korea and achieving independent reunification by the concerted efforts of the Koreans.

U.S. Encroachment on Territorial Sovereignty of Korea under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- It is an unpardonable encroachment upon territorial sovereignty that the United States called some places of south Korea "Florida" and "Hawaii" as it pleases. 
 Rodong Sinmun says this in a signed commentary Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the U.S. has worked hard to Americanize even geographical names of south Korea in a bid to convert it into its permanent colony, the commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Koreans have run the whole gamut of national contempt and humiliation, while their dignity, rights and interests have been mercilessly trampled down by the shameless aggressors, occupiers, for the past more than 60 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fact proves it is not accidental that the U.S. calls south Korea its 51st state. So immeasurable is harm the U.S. did to south Korea, the crime it committed against the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Never should it go unnoticed that the U.S. imperialists renamed some places of south Korea as well as localities of the northern half of Korea their own way, according to the recently disclosed fact. This clearly proves again that the U.S. has long established its Korea policy aimed to put the whole of Korea under its domination and has consistently pursued the policy of aggression against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans keep tabs on the crimes of the U.S. imperialists who have been hell-bent on their policy of aggression against the DPRK, even renaming localities of Korea as they please.

Undying Feats of Kim Jong Il Lauded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun in an article today says Kim Jong Il is a gifted thinker and theoretician who has glorified the revolutionary idea of President Kim Il Sung as the eternal guiding idea of the era of independence with his outstanding ideological and theoretical activities.
 The author of the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The distinguished ideological and theoretical exploits performed by Kim Jong Il in glorifying the revolutionary idea of the President through centuries are, above all, that he gave a scientific formulation to the revolutionary idea of the President, associating it with the august name of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il conducted energetic ideological and theoretical activities to accomplish this historic cause, regarding it as his noblest mission to give a scientific formulation of the revolutionary idea of the President, associating it with his august name. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the course of a comprehensive analysis and review of the hundred year-long history of the development of the revolutionary theories of the working class, he clarified their limitations and gave an scientific and theoretical verification of the originality of the President's revolutionary idea which cannot be measured or construed by the yardsticks of preceding theories and the world-historic position of the idea which reflects the demand of the era of independence and desire of the people and holds the highest place in the history of human thoughts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the national seminar of party information workers on February 19, Juche 63 (1974), he formulated the revolutionary idea of the President with profound logics and classic propositions, associating it with the august name of the President, and declared the program of modeling the whole society on the Juche idea. This was a historic milestone in definitely placing the revolutionary idea of the President in the position of the guiding idea of the era of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has made public a lot of famous works including "On the Juche Idea," "The Juche Philosophy Is an Original Revolutionary Philosophy," "Socialism Is a Science" and "The Songun Revolutionary Line Is a Great Revolutionary Line of Our Times and the Ever-Victorious Banner of Our Revolution" to further develop and enrich the revolutionary idea of the President with new principles and contents. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today, the revolutionary idea of the President is highly praised by progressive humankind as the perfect guiding idea, theory and method of our times and is giving a powerful impetus to the human cause of independence in the 21st century.

DPRK's Holidays Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks, lecture meetings, photo exhibitions and film shows were held in the Czech Republic, South Africa, Ethiopia and Singapore from Sept. 20 to 22 on the occasion of the 61st founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 80th anniversary of the formation of the Down-with-Imperialism Union (DIU).
 On display at the photo exhibitions were pictures showing the undying feats performed by President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il in party building and the might of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean films including "Brilliant History of Great Leadership" were screened at the film shows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of a county committee of the Communist Party of Czech and Moravia of the Czech Republic said at round-table talks that the DIU which was formed 80 years ago was the historic roots of the WPK. The DPRK under the guidance of the most revolutionary party which has inherited the tradition of the DIU is throwing its rays as an invincible socialist bulwark, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of a branch in Pretoria City of the African National Congress of South Africa in a lecture stressed that the WPK has invincible strength as it is guided by the immortal Juche idea which was founded by President Kim Il Sung and is being developed in depth by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairperson of the Addis Ababa Youth Association of Ethiopia, seeing pictures on show, said the WPK has become great fighting ranks carrying the global cause of independence to accomplishment in the van under the wise guidance of General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of a Singaporean company, after watching a Korean film, highly praised Kim Jong Il as a peerlessly great man leading the 21st century with Songun politics.

S. Korean Bellicose Forces' Moves to Develop Latest Type Weapon Flailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- We on behalf of the whole nation desirous of the country's peace and reunification bitterly denounce the south Korean bellicose forces for developing a latest type dangerous weapon in pursuance of confrontation and war between fellow countrymen to serve the U.S. in its moves for a war against the north, while taking issue with the war deterrent of the DPRK for ensuring peace and security of the Korean Peninsula. A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland, said this in a statement on Friday assailing their fresh arms build-up. It said:
 Some time ago, the south Korean military authorities announced that they completed the development of a cruise missile capable of striking major military targets in the DPRK and they are contemplating mass-producing and deploying it at the "Guided Missile Command" in one or two years to come. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said arms build-up is an intolerable provocation as it will push the inter-Korean relations to the phase of confrontation and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation now prevailing on the Korean Peninsula is so alarming that the sovereignty and security of the nation are now seriously infringed upon by the reckless moves of the U.S. to stifle the DPRK and ignite a war against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The prevailing situation requires all the Koreans to turn out in the anti-U.S., anti-war struggle for peace to defend the country's peace and the destiny of the nation under the banner of "By our nation itself." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, the south Korean warlike forces are hell bent on the arms buildup and war exercises against the north as active supporters and accomplices of the U.S. in its moves to stifle the north. These cannot be construed otherwise than hideous crimes against the nation as they force fellow countrymen to fall victim to the nuclear war to be ignited by the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK will never remain a passive on-looker to the reckless confrontation moves of the south Korean warlike forces to step up their dangerous arms buildup against the north in wanton violation of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only stern judgment and merciless punishment of history and the nation await the traitorous forces which bring only misfortune and disasters to the nation, toeing outside forces' policy of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean bellicose forces should behave themselves, mindful that their arms buildup to hurt fellow countrymen would adversely affect the north-south relations and this foolish act would only lead to their self-destruction.

Candlelight Rally of Koreans in Germany 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The Koreans in Germany held a candlelight rally in Berlin on Sept. 24 in support of the 4th grand peace march against the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek, south Korea, according to a news report.
 At the rally speakers denounced the U.S. moves to expand its military base in Phyongthaek and the forcible removal of dwelling houses against human rights, asserting that the Korean nation can neither fall victim to the U.S. military strategy nor allow the Korean Peninsula to be an outpost base for a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of German organizations for peace against war made solidarity speeches at the rally. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that the U.S. is working hard to realize its military strategy for supremacy not only in the Korean Peninsula but also on a worldwide scale. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organizations extend support to the south Korean people in their struggle against the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek and get courage from their struggle, they said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution was adopted at the rally.

Fourth National Korean Wrestling Tournament for "Grand Bull Prize" Opened
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The Fourth National Korean Wrestling Tournament for "Grand Bull Prize" was opened on Thursday at the Korean Wrestling Ground on the Rungra Island in Pyongyang amid interest of the people of the DPRK.
 Participating in the tournament are some 100 players selected from different areas of the country. And they will match in team and individual events. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ground was packed to the full with spectators in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wrestlers from North Phyongan and Kangwon Provinces proved successful in the team event held in the morning. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whenever they won matches by employing special technique, the spectators gave thunderous cheers and applause to the winners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is the topic among Korean wrestling enthusiasts and spectators is who will win the bull. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, it is hard to guess who will be the winner as the tournament is attended by many rising wrestlers as well as ones who had shown good results in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bull to be awarded to the best player weighs nearly one ton. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The finals of the individual event for the grand bull prize will be held on the afternoon of October 2.

4th National Korean Costume Exhibition Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The 4th National Korean Costume Exhibition was held in the Central Youth Hall in Pyongyang from September 26 to 29.
 Participated in the exhibition were units under ministries and national institutions including the Ministry of Light Industry, Ministry of Culture and Ministry of Commerce and Korean costume shops in Pyongyang and local areas, nearly 30 in all. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 800 suits of national clothes including holiday best, wedding dress, daily clothes and children's clothes were displayed there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was visited every day by lots of Pyongyang citizens and Korean costume designers, cutters and needle workers from different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wedding dresses for women exhibited by the Korean Minye General Corporation caught the eyes of the visitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Unlike the wedding dresses of deep color which had been exhibited in the past, the new ones were decorated with magnolia flower patterns and beads on white color ground, the traditional color of the ceremonial dresses. The color and decorations made the wedding dresses more graceful. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Clothing Institute under the Ministry of Light Industry participated in the exhibition with chima and jogori (Korean skirt and coat) with light and soft color which is suitable to the national emotion of the Korean people. They were highly appreciated by the visitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display there were publications and computer multimedia introducing designing and processing methods of the Korean clothes. They included "Various Women's Dresses", "Men's Dresses", "Principle of Designing and Modification" and "Children's Clothes for Spring, Summer, Autumn and Winter".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jong Kun Myong, secretary general of the Korean Costume Association, told the KCNA that the annual exhibition provides a good opportunity to improving the form and decoration of the Korean costume in a varied and beautiful way.

U.S. Branded as World's Biggest Nuclear Criminal
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The United States filled its mainland with nuclear weapons and, as if it were not enough, kept more than 13,000 nuclear weapons overseas. This goes to clearly prove that the U.S. is the world's biggest nuclear criminal in bringing the danger of a nuclear war to the earth, declares Rodong Sinmun in an article Friday.
 The author of the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the results of an investigation made public by the U.S. National Archives recently, the U.S. kept more than 13,000 nuclear weapons deployed in Europe, Asia and other parts of the world in the period of the Cold War in the last century and at least 7,000 of them in Europe, many of which still remain in Germany, Britain and other European countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is raising terrific outcries over "nuclear threat" from other countries, terming their nuclear activities for peaceful purposes "development of nuclear weapons." This is a broad hoax to conceal its own criminal nature and justify its attempts to dominate the world with nuclear weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. nuclear arsenals are filled to overflowing with more than 20,000 nuclear weapons of all types. They include over 5,400 intercontinental ballistic missile warheads and more than 1,750 nuclear bombs and cruise missile warheads. The U.S. Defense Department in its 2002 report on nuclear posture decided to resume researches into nuclear weapons which it had suspended for 10 years since 1992 and allocated 6.3 billion U.S. dollars to the nuclear weapons program in fiscal 2004. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citing facts to prove that the U.S. imperialists are nuclear war fanatics bent on inflicting nuclear disasters upon humankind, the article stresses: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The increasing danger of a nuclear war comes from the U.S. attempts at preemptive nuclear attack and its reckless moves to launch a nuclear war. The world public opinion is getting assertive that the U.S. should stand trial for seeking to bring nuclear disasters to humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are the most dangerous force of nuclear war and an enemy common to humankind endangering its existence. The world peace-loving people should wage a dynamic struggle to foil the U.S. imperialists' aggressive and belligerent nuclear policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. had better stop its criminal moves to inflict a nuclear holocaust upon humankind.
